strings.string: \rThis hallway is shabby and well used. It looks more like the entrance to a fort than the legendary Spade's Casino.\r
\rThe inside of Spade's Casino is even more run down than the hallway. The rugs are worn through and the walls need a new coat of paint.\r
\rThe chandelier looks as if it has gotten stuck in the center of several gunfights.\r
\rCome on over and play. You can't win if you don't play.\r
\rThis wood and steel door is locked.\r
\rSorry ranger, but the door is still closed.\r
\rPeople with money are always welcome here.\r
\rYou don't really look like you have enough money to play here.\r
\rOpen your eyes! You just fell through a hatch in the floor.\r
\rYou don't have enough money to play.\r
\rLights flash, bells ring and the bells, cherries and lemons go spinning around.\r
\rA Winner!! Listen to the sound of coins in the tray.\r
\rSorry, you lose. Try again. You are due to hit the jackpot anytime now.\r
\rThe Bar is made of solid oak. Very rare nowadays.\r
\rHey! Only one of you can play at a time, The rest watch!\r
\rDown you go in to the dark hole.\r
\rOh No! You slipped and have fallen down the hole.\r
\rHand over hand you slowly climb up the rope.\r
\rYou won! Good betting on your part.\r
\rYou lose! Better luck next time.\r
\rHey! Don't climb on the table.\r
\rThis table is some cloth covered wood over a pair of sawhorses.\r
This bum looks at you through bloodshot eyes.\r
The young lady is offended by the way you are looking at her.\r
The young poor couple looks at you through tearful eyes.\r
This well-dressed man looks like he knows what he is doing.\r
You are being checked out very carefully.\r
This guy can barely roll the dice.\r
The well-dressed worker looks very bored.\r
My my, what a fancy dresser you see here.\r
This guy doesn't look very friendly.\r
The guard leader is a real mean looking dude.\r
This slot machine player looks like she will kill if you try to take her place.\r
\rThis door was on the losing end of a fist fight.\r
\rThis door is open.\r
\rA few smoking pieces are all that remain of this door.\r
Would you like to play the slot machine at $10 per pull?\r\r\x11\x10Yes\r\x10No\r
Y
N
Read paragraph 96.\rWould you like to play 3 card monty?\r\r\x11\x10Yes\r\x10No\r
Read paragraph 139.\rWould you like to play High / Low?\r\r\x11\x10Yes\r\x10No\r
\rYou have landed in the "wine" cellar.\r
\rYou are behind the bar.\r
\rYou are going up the stairs.\r
\rYou are going down the stairs.\r
\rHigh rollers are always welcome at Spade's casino. Please come again.\r
\rThe brick walls make this place look like a fortress.\r
This man looks pretty lucky.\r
This man is very greedy.\r
Gus, the happy barkeep, wouldn't hurt a fly.\r
\rAh fresh air! You can breathe again as you climb out through a one-way passage from under Spade's Casino.\r
\rYou are escorted back to the casino.\r
\rThe old bed crumbles and falls to pieces at your touch.\r
\rThe shelves and all the books on them fall apart when you look at them.\r
\rThis unused wine cellar is full of old dusty shelves.\r
\rOn the shelf before you are some dusty bottles.\r
\rScattered about the floor is rubble, junk and trash.\r
\rRead paragraph 71.\r\r\r
\rThis sound-proof door is made of steel and aluminum.\r
\rThese shelves shake when you walk into them but they are still standing.\r
\rThe rubble blocking your way looks like it could be dug out of the way.\r
\rThis pile of loose rocks and rubble blocks your path.\r
\rThis old boarded over shaft goes down into the darkness below.\r
\rA rope tied overhead goes down in to the hole at your feet and stretches out of sight.\r
\rA rope hangs down from a large hole in the ceiling.\r
\rYour feet kick up dust as you walk through piles of trash and wood.\r
\rThe cards are being shuffled.\r
\rWhoops! You just slipped and fell on the loose gravel.\r
\rWe have a winner. See folks, anyone can win.\r
\rOops! Sorry you lose.\r
\rSure you can play, but we only have room for one more.\r
\rYour way is blocked by a rock fall so old it is as hard as cement.\r
\rThis pile of dust looks very strange...\r
\rThe graffiti scrawl reads TIN MAN WAS HERE.\r
Big Al gives you a dirty look.\r
That Mac 17 looks awfully big in that cute girl's hand.\r
\r"Hey! Youse don't belong in here. Da game's down da hall."\r
\rThis bathroom is out of place. It is far too beautiful and clean from what you have seen of Spade's.\r
\rThis table is very impressive. Made of solid wood and covered in bright red cloth.\r
\rYou have spotted something strange here...\r
\rThis is a rigged table. The dealer can see all the cards.\r
\rAs big and beautiful as this bathroom is, there is only enough room for one person.\r
\rA piercing scream fills the air as Kutie yells her war cry.\r
\rLittle Al's bed is the softest and biggest you have ever seen, and totally out of place here at Spade's.\r
\rOops! You stepped on a squeaky board.\r
\r"Kill that noisemaker in the hall, boys."\r
"You aren't allowed in here!"\r
\rYou are now standing on the bar.\r
\rWhat are you doing to that bar?\r
\rYou stand at the bar hoping to get a drink and wait.. and wait...\rFinally a pit boss comes over to you. Read paragraph 83.\r
\rThis is an old style fallout shelter from way before the war. No one has been here in years.\r
\rYou silently step over the squeaky board.\r
\rYou spot a squeaky board just ahead. Better move silently or you'll be heard.\r
